  "caption": "Classic smoking/lung-cancer confounding SCM with LaTeX-style variable symbols. Inherited/family risk G_f, age cohort C_a, and socioeconomic context S_u are pre-exposure common causes of smoking exposure A_s and lung cancer Y_c, opening backdoor paths such as A_s <- G_f -> Y_c, A_s <- C_a -> Y_c, and A_s <- S_u -> Y_c. Smoking also acts through tar or airway injury M_t, while socioeconomic context contributes through occupational exposure E_o. Estimating the causal effect of A_s on Y_c requires blocking the pre-exposure backdoor paths without conditioning away the mediator M_t. Solid arrows are structural data-generating links. This is a data-generating schematic; it is not fitted causal discovery, model performance evidence, or biological localization."
